<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-08-17T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-08-17T15:00:00-05:00" n="184" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d184">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">813.00 Tacoma/–: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Honduras</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Morales</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tegucigalpa</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-08-17T14:00:00-06:00"><hi rend="italic">August 17, 1922—2
                                    p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 9:40 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>70. Referring to the Department’s telegram 28, August 15, 2[<hi rend="italic">5</hi>] p.m. The President assured me that he will
                                bring up the boundary question at the conference and attempt to
                                arrive at a solution.</p>
                            <p>In company with the President and party I shall leave for Amapala on
                                the 18th instant to attend the conference.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Morales</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>